---
import ArticleLayout from '../../layouts/ArticleLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<ArticleLayout
  title="Christmas Book Recommendations 2025"
  author="Gregory the Great Institute"
  date="December 2025"
  category="Resource"
  image="/images/art/roestraten-still-life-books.jpg"
  imageAlt="Still Life of Books by Pseudo-Roestraten"
  related={[
    { title: "The Abolition of Man Study Guide", href: `${base}library/abolition-of-man-guide/`, meta: "Resource · GGI" },
    { title: "5 Ways to Celebrate Easter as a Family", href: `${base}library/easter-family/`, meta: "Resource · Catherine Renneberg" },
  ]}
>
  <p>
    Each year, the Gregory the Great Institute curates a list of books worth giving — and
    reading — during the Christmas season. These are not bestsellers or beach reads. They
    are books that reward careful attention, that deepen the mind and the spirit, and that
    make excellent gifts for the thoughtful reader in your life.
  </p>

  <p>
    Our 2025 list draws from theology, philosophy, literature, and history — the traditions
    that have shaped Catholic culture for centuries and continue to offer wisdom for our time.
  </p>

  <div class="resource-download">
    <a href="#" class="resource-download__btn">Download Christmas Book Recommendations</a>
    <p class="resource-download__note">Free PDF · No signup required</p>
  </div>
</ArticleLayout>

<style>
  .resource-download {
    background: var(--color-linen);
    border: 1px solid rgba(198, 160, 50, 0.3);
    border-radius: 3px;
    padding: 28px;
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 28px;
  }

  .resource-download__btn {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: 12px 28px;
    background: var(--color-crimson);
    color: white;
    border-radius: 3px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: background var(--transition-fast);
  }

  .resource-download__btn:hover {
    background: #6b1d00;
  }

  .resource-download__note {
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--color-gray);
    margin-top: 8px;
  }
</style>
